tion that ends in a decision. This book gives you that how. Investing in Financial Research is a guidebook for conducting financial investigations and lays out Cheryl Strauss Einhorn's AREA Method—a research and decision-making system that uniquely controls for bias, focuses on the incentives of others and expands knowledge while improving judgement—and applies it to investigating financial situations. AREA is applicable to all sorts of financial sleuthing, whether for investment analysis or investigative journalism. It allows you to be the expert in your own life. The AREA Method provides you with: *Defined tasks that guide and focus your research on your vision of success; *A structure that isolates your sources, giving you insight into their perspectives, biases and incentives; *Investigative resources, tips and techniques to upgrade your research and analysis beyond document-based sources; *Exercises to foster creativity and originality in your thinking; *A sequence and framework that brings your disparate pieces of research together to build your confidence and conviction about your financial decision.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aDecision makingxMethodologyvProblems, exercises, etc. 0aFinancexDecision makingxMethodology. 0aFinancexResearchxMethodology. 0aResearchxMethodologyvProblems, exercises, etc. 4aBusiness (General). 4aGeneral Economics. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Finance / Financial Engineering.2bisacsh1 aBlair, Tony.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065198008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBO